# Task Management

All tasks are managed centrally in the **haderach-tasks** repo at `../haderach-tasks/` using [taskmd](https://github.com/driangle/taskmd). This app repo does not have its own tasks directory.

## Creating a task from this repo

Write the task file to `../haderach-tasks/` with `group: vendors` and `phase: vendors` in the frontmatter. Follow the taskmd format and conventions defined in `haderach-tasks/.cursor/rules/todo-conventions.mdc`.

Use plain integer IDs with no leading zeros (e.g., `"7"` not `"007"`). Check existing files in `../haderach-tasks/` to determine the next available ID.

If the task is ambiguous about which app it belongs to (e.g., cross-cutting infra work), prompt the user to specify the `group` value (`card`, `stocks`, `home`, `vendors`, `admin`, `agent`, or `platform`).

## Reading tasks

When the user references a task by number (e.g., "task 29"), look it up in `../haderach-tasks/` by matching the `id` field or filename prefix (e.g., `29-*.md`). All tasks across all apps live there — the referenced task may belong to any group, not just `vendors`.

To see tasks for this app, read files in `../haderach-tasks/` where the `group` frontmatter field is `vendors`. Only read tasks where `status` is `pending` or `in-progress` unless specifically asked about others.

## Task dashboard

To start the taskmd web dashboard, run from the tasks repo:

```sh
cd ../haderach-tasks && taskmd web start --dir . --open --port 4173
```
